		}]


	}, {
		id: "000000000000EF25"
		x: 0.0d
		y: 6.0d
		dependencies: ["000000000000BD01"]
		title: "Cities of the Continent"
		icon: {id: "minecraft:map", Count: 1b}
		description: ["Five major novel-accurate cities generate across the world: Suotuo City (trade hub, near spawn), Heaven Dou City (imperial capital, 80-block radius with academy and cathedral), Star Luo City (military capital), Spirit City (Spirit Hall HQ), and the merchant city Silvers.", "Additional cities spawn at 12% frequency. Each features merchants, cultivator guards, and faction-themed architecture. Shrek Academy and a Tournament Arena also generate as standalone structures. Explore along with your Waystone network — the cities are the best source of NPC trades, sect recruitment, and alchemy recipe discovery."]
		tasks: [{
			id: "000000000000EF26"
			type: "checkmark"
			title: "Locate any major Soul Land city and visit its market district"
		}]
		rewards: [{
			id: "000000000000EF27"
			type: "item"
			item: {id: "waystones:waystone", Count: 1b}
		}]
	}, {
		id: "000000000000EF28"
		x: 2.0d
		y: 6.0d
		dependencies: ["000000000000EF25"]
		title: "Join a Sect"
		icon: {id: "soulland:cultivation_manual", Count: 1b}
		description: ["Six sects operate across the continent, each offering unique percentage bonuses, four internal ranks, a mission board, and a contribution point economy. The sect you join is a permanent affiliation that gates certain item trades and passive buffs.", "Find a sect headquarters in a city (each city has its own affiliated sect). Speak to the Sect Elder to join. Rank up through missions and contribution points. The bonuses at high rank are not trivial — a maxed-out sect affiliation provides flat combat boosts that compound with everything else."]
		tasks: [{
			id: "000000000000EF29"
			type: "checkmark"
			title: "Join a sect and reach at least Rank 2 within it"
		}]
		rewards: [{
			id: "000000000000EF2A"
			type: "item"
			item: {id: "mmorpg:stone/2", Count: 2b}
		}]
	}, {
		id: "000000000000EF2B"
		x: 4.0d
		y: 6.0d
		dependencies: ["000000000000BD01"]
		title: "Spirit Hall Standing"
		icon: {id: "soulland:cultivation_manual", Count: 1b}
		description: ["The Spirit Hall is the dominant political faction of the continent — and a morally ambiguous one. Its reputation system runs from -100 to +100 across 7 standing levels.", "Positive standing unlocks trades and protection. Negative standing (below -25) triggers escalating consequences: bounty notices at level 1-5, assassination squads above that. The Spirit Hall will actively pursue players who oppose it too openly. Play both sides or commit. Neutrality is also a choice."]
		tasks: [{
			id: "000000000000EF2C"
			type: "checkmark"
			title: "Interact with the Spirit Hall faction and check your standing"
		}]
		rewards: [{
			id: "000000000000EF2D"
			type: "item"
			item: {id: "soulland:spirit_condensing_pill", Count: 2b}
		}]
	}, {
		id: "000000000000EF2E"
		x: 6.0d
		y: 6.0d
		dependencies: ["000000000000BD01"]
		title: "The Beast Contract"
		icon: {id: "soulland:spirit_detector", Count: 1b}
		description: ["Spirit Beasts can be contracted as permanent companions. The contract system allows up to 2 bound beasts at a time, and companions persist through server restarts — they\'re not temporary summons.", "To contract a beast: weaken it below 20% health without killing it, then offer a Contract item crafted at the Forging Table. The beast\'s soul power and age determine how useful it becomes as a companion. Bring something you hunted at the Inner Forest or deeper — surface beasts are too weak to contribute to endgame fights."]
		tasks: [{
			id: "000000000000EF2F"
			type: "checkmark"
			title: "Contract a Spirit Beast companion (max 2 active)"
		}]
		rewards: [{
			id: "000000000000EF30"
			type: "item"
			item: {id: "soulland:foundation_pill", Count: 3b}
		}]
	}, {
		id: "000000000000EF31"
		x: 8.0d
		y: 6.0d
		dependencies: ["000000000000EF2E"]
		title: "Spirit Bone"
		icon: {id: "soulland:soul_crystal", Count: 1b}
		description: ["Spirit Bones drop from boss-variant spirit beasts — the same tier that the Ancient Spirit Incense (found on the support track) summons. Bones have five evolution stages, with stat scaling at each.", "At stage 3, a per-slot passive ability unlocks — unique to the slot the bone occupies (head, body, limb, etc.). Stage 5 is endgame-level stat contribution. Collect and evolve a full set over time. Each slot\'s passive stacks with your M&S stats, Apotheosis gems, and soul ring skills simultaneously."]
		tasks: [{
			id: "000000000000EF32"
			type: "checkmark"
			title: "Obtain and evolve a Spirit Bone to at least Stage 2"
		}]
		rewards: [{
			id: "000000000000EF33"
			type: "item"
			item: {id: "mmorpg:stone/3", Count: 2b}
		}]


	}, {
		id: "000000000000EF34"
		x: 10.0d
		y: 2.0d
		dependencies: ["000000000000A043"]
		title: "Herb Refinement Ritual"
		icon: {id: "soulland:wild_herb", Count: 1b}
		description: ["Hold-to-channel on any Spirit Herb to begin the Herb Refinement Ritual. A visual progress bar appears. Common herbs channel in 0.4 seconds; Legendary variants take up to 8 seconds.", "Refined consumption extracts more of the herb\'s Qi content and reduces foundation instability gain compared to quick-consuming. For any herb rarer than Uncommon, always use the ritual. The difference in soul power gain is measurable."]
		tasks: [{
			id: "000000000000EF35"
			type: "checkmark"
			title: "Use the Herb Refinement Ritual on a Spirit Herb (hold to channel)"
		}]
		rewards: [{
